      <exercise id="id9523685">
        <problem id="id1168372398980">
          <para id="id9511073">Below are the points (–2,4) and (–5,–3).</para><para id="element-643"><media id="id6097819" alt="A picture of the points (–2,4) and (–5,–3)."><image src="../../media/1g.PNG" mime-type="image/png" print-width="3in"/></media></para><list id="element-950" list-type="labeled-item" mark-suffix=".">
<item><label>a</label>How far is it <emphasis>across</emphasis> from one to the other (the horizontal line in the drawing)?</item>
<item><label>b</label>How far is it <emphasis>down</emphasis> from one to the other (the vertical line in the drawing)?</item>
<item><label>c</label>How far are the two points from each other?</item>
<item><label>d</label>What is the <emphasis>midpoint</emphasis> of the diagonal line?</item></list>
        </problem>
      </exercise>
      
      
      
      
      
